I think I agree with Mr. Tanizaki that, in interior design, it is vulgar and in bad taste to try to hide the cables of electric lamps, windfans, and other type of domestic machinery. If you are not comfortable seeing it, this means that you are only hiding the problem.

A light bulb and the cable leading up and right to it - it feels somehow comforting - you see the mechanism, you see where the electricity flows through, you understand how it works. Hiding the cable behind a wall or roofing just invites unnecessary discomfort and insecurity.
